# TradeFeed — Cursor AI Project Rules

## Project Overview
TradeFeed (www.tradefeed.co.za) is a South African e-commerce platform that lets sellers create professional product catalogs and receive orders via WhatsApp. Hosted on Vercel. Solo developer project.

## Tech Context
- Frontend: Next.js (React) with TypeScript
- Hosting: Vercel
- Payments: PayFast (South African gateway)
- Target Market: South African wholesalers, retailers, and informal sellers
- Currency: South African Rand (ZAR / R)
- Primary User Flow: Seller creates catalog → shares link → buyer browses → orders via WhatsApp

## Design System
- Theme: Dark mode primary (#1A1A1A background, #F5F5F5 text)
- Brand Color: Emerald Green (#25D366) — used for CTAs, accents, highlights
- Secondary Accent: Purple (#8A2BE2) for highlights
- Font: System sans-serif (consider migrating to Inter or Poppins)
- Mobile-first responsive design — most SA users are on mobile
- Minimize data usage — optimize images, lazy load, compress assets

## Code Standards
- Write clean, modular TypeScript with proper types
- Use server components where possible for performance
- Keep bundle size minimal — SA users have expensive data
- All user-facing text must be simple, clear English (many users are not native English speakers)
- All prices in ZAR (R) format, e.g., R199.00
- WhatsApp integration is core — always use wa.me links with pre-filled messages
- POPIA compliant — always handle user data with consent, never share without permission

## Current Pricing Tiers
- Free: R0/month — up to 20 products, 10 AI generations, basic analytics
- Starter: R99/month — unlimited products, 25 AI generations, promoted listings, buyer reviews
- Pro: R299/month — unlimited everything, priority support, team accounts, advanced analytics

## Key Features
- AI-powered product listing (photo → listing)
- WhatsApp checkout (pre-filled order messages)
- Public marketplace for product discovery
- Seller analytics and revenue dashboard
- Order tracking
- Product variants (size, color, etc.)
- CSV bulk import
- CDN image hosting
- Verified seller badges
- Buyer reviews and ratings

## Growth Priorities (March–December 2026)
Goal: 10,000 users, 1,000 paid users by end of 2026.
Always prioritize features that:
1. Reduce onboarding friction
2. Drive free-to-paid conversion
3. Create viral/sharing loops
4. Make the tool "sticky" (hard to leave)

## When Writing Code
- Always consider mobile performance first
- Minimize API calls and database queries
- Use optimistic UI updates where possible
- Handle WhatsApp deep links correctly for both iOS and Android
- Always include loading states and error handling
- Write accessible HTML (aria-labels, proper contrast, semantic elements)
- Keep components reusable and composable
